SIMPLE: honey_flower
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: honey flower
<hw>honey flower</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An erect bushy shrub (<spn>Lambertia
formosa</spn>) of eastern Australia having terminal clusters of red
flowers yielding much nectar.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> mountain devil, <spn>Lambertia
formosa</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The Australian shrub (<spn>Protea
mellifera</spn>) whose flowers yield honey copiously.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> <spn>Protea mellifera</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <def>An evergreen shrub of the genus
<gen>Melianthus</gen>, a native of the Cape of Good Hope. The flowers
yield much honey.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Honeyless</ent>⟦br⟧
